.\" termin.al-name: clear
.\" termin.al-usage: clear
.\" termin.al-summary: Clear terminal scrollback.
.TH CLEAR 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
clear \- Clear terminal scrollback.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
clear
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Removes the visible terminal transcript from the current shell pane. It does not close an inline viewer because clear runs only from the shell presentation.
.SH OUTPUT
No text is printed. The clear-scrollback effect is applied after the command succeeds.
.SH FAILURES
Any argument is rejected and leaves the scrollback unchanged.
.SH NOTES
Command history, the current virtual directory, other panes, pane layout and browser theme preference are preserved. The cleared transcript is not recoverable through history because history stores command sources, not prior output.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ clear
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
history(1), pane(1), pwd(1)
